[0.001, "o", "                                                                                                         \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mTheory: this process is using normal Python internals and the current heap samples missed script-specific buffers. Best next\u001b[m  \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mtarget is stack or the anonymous 18 MB mapping at 7f14711fe000, where live strings and decoded data often sit. If you want,\u001b[m   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mIÔÇÖll read the stack next.\u001b[0m                                                                                                     \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[1;38;2;0;255;136myouÔØ» \u001b[0mmap the memory                                                                                                           \u001b[K\r\n   \u001b[38;2;255;68;68mÔêÖÔêÖÔùÅ\u001b[0m \u001b[3;38;2;255;102;85mScanning system snapshot...\u001b[0m                                                                                             \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[1;38;2;0;255;136mÔØ» \u001b[0m\u001b[7ma\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;240msk godshell something...\u001b[0m                                                                                                   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;85;85;85mCtrl+([r]efresh [s]ave [l]oad [p]anel) type help for more info, Esc to toggle focus\u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;68;68;68m 100%\u001b[0m                                      \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;0;255;136m[sel:bash ./launch_test_agent.sh/264057]\u001b[0m                                                                                      \u001b[K\u001b[33;H"]
