[0.233, "o", "\u001b[H\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m555d94b80000 exposes the socket.getaddrinfo docstring text ÔÇ£Resolve host and port into list of address info entries...ÔÇØ,\u001b[m      \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mwhich is consistent with inspect/get_maps showing Python with socket module loaded.\u001b[0m                                           \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mLarge parts of the heap are sparse or zeroed at the sampled offsets. Evidence: 555d94b00000 and most of 555d94be0000 are\u001b[m      \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mzero-filled; 555d94a80000 looks like Python object/bytecode data and pointers, but no clear URLs, commands, or credentials\u001b[m    \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204min that window.\u001b[0m                                                                                                               \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mTheory: this process is using normal Python internals and the current heap samples missed script-specific buffers. Best next\u001b[m  \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mtarget is stack or the anonymous 18 MB mapping at 7f14711fe000, where live strings and decoded data often sit. If you want,\u001b[m   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mIÔÇÖll read the stack next.\u001b[0m                                                                                                     \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[1;38;2;0;255;136myouÔØ» \u001b[0mmap the memory                                                                                                           \u001b[K\r\n   \u001b[48;2;204;34;0m \u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;255;255;255;48;2;204;34;0mÔûñ get_maps\u001b[0m\u001b[48;2;204;34;0m \u001b[0m  \u001b[3;38;2;153;153;153mPID 264057 ┬À 59 regions ┬À heap ┬À stack ┬À 32 libs mapped\u001b[0m                                                       \u001b[K\r\n   \u001b[48;2;204;34;0m \u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;255;255;255;48;2;204;34;0mÔºë get_libraries\u001b[0m\u001b[48;2;204;34;0m \u001b[0m  \u001b[3;38;2;153;153;153m5 shared libraries ┬À linux-vdso.so.1, libpython3.14.so.1.0, libc.so.6\u001b[0m                                    \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[1;38;2;255;68;68mgodshellÔØ» \u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;204;204;204mMemory is mapped like a normal Python process with one notable executable-writable page. Evidence: get_maps shows\u001b[m   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m/usr/bin/python3.14, [heap] at 555d94a3b000-555d94bf4000, a large 18 MB anonymous region at 7f14711fe000-7f1472400000, stack\u001b[m  \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mat 7ffef85a1000-7ffef85c2000, and a single rwxp page at 7f1473204000-7f1473205000.\u001b[0m                                            \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mNo suspicious injected shared object is visible. Evidence: get_libraries resolves only libpython3.14, libc, libm, and the\u001b[m     \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mloader; get_maps also shows expected Python extension modules _socket, _struct, and _ctypes.\u001b[0m                                  \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mBest targets now:\u001b[0m                                                                                                             \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m1. rwxp page 7f1473204000 for shellcode/JIT-like content\u001b[0m                                                                      \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m2. stack 7ffef85a1000 for argv, env fragments, live strings\u001b[0m                                                                   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m3. large anonymous region 7f14711fe000 for decoded buffers\u001b[0m                                                                    \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m4. more heap around 555d94a3b000-555d94bf4000 for script data\u001b[0m                                                                 \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m"]
